description.narrative:
UNICEF continued to support the Ministry of Health (MoH) in 2019 to: strengthen the national health system, with a focus on maternal and child care; enhance national health care programmes, especially immunization; and strengthen community and primary health care for the most vulnerable children. A key result was the 3 per cent increase in children receiving the first dose of measles vaccine, to which UNICEF contributed with catch-up campaigns, communication campaigns and development of methodologies for emergency vaccination.
